ITV.Tour.de.France.2014.Stage.14.Highlights.PDTV.x264-NX

Saturday 19th July 2014 ITV4
7pm to 8pm Highlights

Highlights of stage 14 - the second and last day in the Alps - a 177km route which starts climbing almost from the start. The riders cross first the legendary peaks of the Lautaret and the Izoard before a summit finish at Risoul which has already reared its fearsome head this year in the Tour de l'Avenir and the Criterium du Dauphine. Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary by Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting the reporter at the roadside.
